                  </persName>
            . I live with a pawnbroker; I produce a counterpane and a piece of linen, pawned on the 7th of March, for four shillings by the prisoner.</p>
               <p>The property produced and identified.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. My wife and I fell out; I got a drop of liquor in my head; I thought I could make free from knowing him, I did pledge them.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18090412-112-verdict670" type="verdictDescription">
